Flowtriq DDoS Detection - Splunk Technology Add-on
===================================================

Receive and analyze DDoS detection events sent from Flowtriq via
Splunk HTTP Event Collector (HEC).

Provides:
  - Field extractions for flowtriq:incident sourcetype
  - Lookup tables for severity levels and attack families
  - Event types and tags for CIM compatibility
  - Overview dashboard with attack timeline, top attack types,
    severity distribution, targeted nodes, and recent incidents

Requirements:
  - Splunk Enterprise 8.0+ or Splunk Cloud
  - Flowtriq dashboard with Splunk HEC integration configured
  - A HEC token configured to accept the flowtriq:incident sourcetype

Setup:
  1. Install this add-on on your Splunk search head
  2. Create a HEC token in Splunk (Settings > Data Inputs > HTTP Event Collector)
  3. Set the sourcetype to flowtriq:incident on the HEC token
  4. In Flowtriq, go to Settings > Integrations > Splunk HEC
  5. Enter your Splunk HEC URL and token
  6. Events will flow on attack_start and attack_end

Fields extracted:
  event_type, incident_id, severity, attack_family, peak_pps,
  peak_bps, source_ip_count, confidence, status, started_at,
  resolved_at, node_name, node_ip, dashboard_url

Support: support@flowtriq.com
